---
import {
    AnnouncementBar,
    TextCardSection,
    Container,
} from '@components/odyssey-theme';
import Layout from '../../layouts/Page.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/forms/ContactForm.astro';

const seo = {
    title: 'FAQ | SCI-NAD',
    description: 'Frequently Asked Questions about SCI-NAD',
};

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is SCI-NAD?",
    answer: "SCI-NAD is an advanced platform aimed at making neurotechnology accessible to everyone. Our goal is to simplify brain-electrode interactions and gamify neuroengineering education."
  },
  {
    question: "Who is SCI-NAD for?",
    answer: "SCI-NAD is designed for researchers, engineers, students, and enthusiasts in neuroscience and neuroengineering. Whether you're an expert or just getting started, our platform provides tools to help you learn and innovate."
  },
  {
    question: "How can I use SCI-NAD?",
    answer: "You can use SCI-NAD to build, visualize, and simulate neural networks and brain interactions in 3D, explore neural data, and test your own hypotheses through our platform's intelligent knowledge graphs and decoding pipelines."
  },
  {
    question: "What are the key features of SCI-NAD?",
    answer: "SCI-NAD offers a 3D brain mapping tool, neural decoders, an intuitive interface for building neural montages, knowledge graphs, and annotated research papers to help streamline your neuroengineering projects."
  },
  {
    question: "How can I get started?",
    answer: "Sign up for early access through our website. We offer onboarding materials, tutorials, and a step-by-step guide to help you get started with SCI-NAD."
  }
];
---

<Layout {seo}>
    <AnnouncementBar
        text="Have questions? Find answers in our FAQ!"
        href="/support/faq"
        slot="announcement-bar"
    />
    
    <Container>
        <TextCardSection id="faq-section">
            <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
            <p>Below you will find answers to the most common questions regarding our platform, mission, and features.</p>
            
            {faqs.map(faq => (
                <details>
                    <summary>{faq.question}</summary>
                    <p>{faq.answer}</p>
                </details>
            ))}

            <h2>Need further assistance?</h2>
            <p>Contact us through the form below, and our team will be happy to assist you with any other questions or inquiries.</p>

            <ContactForm />
        </TextCardSection>
    </Container>
</Layout>

<style>
    details {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        padding: 1rem;
        background-color: var(--theme-surface-1);
        border-radius: var(--theme-shape-radius);
    }
    summary {
        font-weight: bold;
        cursor: pointer;
    }
    details p {
        margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    h1, h2 {
        font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    p {
        font-size: var(--font-size-md);
        margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;
    }
</style>

<!-- Additional FAQ Content -->
<section>
    <h2>Additional Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <details>
        <summary>What is SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD (Synaptic Computational Interface for NeuroAdvancement Design) is an innovative platform that democratizes access to neurotechnology. It offers an interactive 3D brain mapping tool combined with real-time neural simulations, making neurotech accessible and engaging for everyoneâ€”from experts to enthusiasts.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>Who is SCI-NAD designed for?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD is designed for two primary user groups:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Neurotech Experts and Researchers:</strong> Professionals who require advanced tools for precision work in neuroscience and neurotechnology.</li>
            <li><strong>Students and Enthusiasts:</strong> Individuals interested in neurotechnology who seek an intuitive and interactive learning experience without needing prior expertise.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>Do I need prior experience in neuroscience or neurotechnology to use SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>No prior experience is necessary. SCI-NAD is built with an intuitive interface and gamified learning pathways that guide users from novice to expert levels. Whether you're a seasoned professional or just curious about the brain, SCI-NAD is accessible to all.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>What are the key features of SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>- <strong>Interactive 3D Brain Mapping Tool:</strong> Visualize and interact with a ball-and-stick model of the brain, placing electrodes and targeting specific regions.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Real-Time Neural Simulations:</strong> Run simulations to see how the brain responds to electrode placements and neural activity.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Drag-and-Drop Interface:</strong> Easily create 3D montages and neural pathways without a steep learning curve.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Knowledge Graphs & Contextual Annotations:</strong> Link research papers, datasets, and scientific content directly to your visual models.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Gamified Learning Pathways:</strong> Progress through levels to deepen your understanding and unlock advanced features.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Cloud-Based Accessibility:</strong> Use SCI-NAD across devices with seamless performance, thanks to cloud integration.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How does SCI-NAD make neurotechnology accessible?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD simplifies complex neurotech concepts through intuitive visualizations and interactive tools. The platform's gamified learning approach and user-friendly interface eliminate barriers, allowing anyone to explore and understand brain-electrode interactions and neural data.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>Can I import my own data into SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>Yes, SCI-NAD supports the integration of FAIR (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, Reusable) neural datasets, including NWB (Neurodata Without Borders) formats. You can import your data to run custom simulations, analyses, and visualizations.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How do the real-time neural simulations work?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD utilizes advanced technologies like NVIDIA Omniverse and NeuralVDB to render ultra-fast 3D simulations. When you place electrodes or adjust parameters, the platform computes neural responses in real-time, providing immediate visual feedback on brain activity.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>What technologies power SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD is built on a robust tech stack, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>NVIDIA Omniverse & OpenUSD:</strong> For high-performance 3D rendering and simulations.</li>
            <li><strong>FreeSurfer & Nengo:</strong> For brain model importing and neural activity simulation.</li>
            <li><strong>Cloud Services (AWS, Vercel, GCP):</strong> Ensuring scalability and low-latency performance.</li>
            <li><strong>Programming Languages:</strong> Core components developed in C++, Rust, and Python for optimal performance.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>Is SCI-NAD available on multiple platforms?</summary>
        <p>Yes, SCI-NAD is designed for cross-platform deployment. You can access it on desktop computers, tablets, and mobile devices, ensuring flexibility and convenience.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How can I get started with SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>Getting started is easy:</p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Sign Up:</strong> Create an account on our website.</li>
            <li><strong>Explore the Tutorial:</strong> Begin with our guided tutorials to familiarize yourself with the interface and features.</li>
            <li><strong>Start Exploring:</strong> Use the 3D brain mapping tool, place electrodes, and run simulations.</li>
            <li><strong>Join the Community:</strong> Engage with other users, share your work, and learn from collaborative projects.</li>
        </ol>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>Is there a cost to use SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD offers a tiered pricing model to accommodate different user needs:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Free Tier:</strong> Access basic features, including the 3D brain mapping tool and standard simulations.</li>
            <li><strong>Premium Subscription:</strong> Unlock advanced features like importing custom datasets, advanced simulations, and priority support.</li>
            <li><strong>Educational and Research Licenses:</strong> Special pricing and features for institutions and research organizations.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Please visit our <strong>Pricing</strong> page for detailed information.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How does SCI-NAD ensure scientific accuracy?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD collaborates with neuroscientists and leverages validated tools like FreeSurfer and Nengo for accurate brain models and neural simulations. We continuously update our platform with the latest research and methodologies to maintain scientific integrity.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>Can educators use SCI-NAD in teaching?</summary>
        <p>Absolutely! SCI-NAD is an excellent tool for educators:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Interactive Learning:</strong> Engage students with hands-on simulations and visualizations.</li>
            <li><strong>Curriculum Integration:</strong> Aligns with neuroscience and neurotech courses.</li>
            <li><strong>Educational Resources:</strong> Access to tutorials, lesson plans, and support materials.</li>
            <li><strong>Collaboration Tools:</strong> Share projects and assignments with students within the platform.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>Is there a community or forum for users?</summary>
        <p>Yes, SCI-NAD fosters a collaborative community where users can:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Share Simulations and Models:</strong> Upload and download user-generated content.</li>
            <li><strong>Collaborate on Projects:</strong> Work together on simulations and research.</li>
            <li><strong>Ask Questions and Get Support:</strong> Access forums and support channels for assistance.</li>
            <li><strong>Stay Updated:</strong> Receive news on the latest features, updates, and events.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How does SCI-NAD handle privacy and data security?</summary>
        <p>We take privacy and security seriously:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Data Encryption:</strong> All user data is encrypted in transit and at rest.</li>
            <li><strong>Compliance Standards:</strong> Adherence to GDPR and other relevant data protection regulations.</li>
            <li><strong>User Control:</strong> You have full control over your data and can manage privacy settings within your account.</li>
            <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> We perform regular security audits to safeguard our platform.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How can I contribute to SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>There are several ways to contribute:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Provide Feedback:</strong> Share your experiences and suggestions to help us improve.</li>
            <li><strong>Develop Content:</strong> Create and share your own simulations, models, or tutorials.</li>
            <li><strong>Join the Team:</strong> Check our <strong>Careers</strong> page for opportunities to work with us.</li>
            <li><strong>Community Engagement:</strong> Participate in forums, answer questions, and help other users.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How is SCI-NAD different from other neurotech platforms?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD stands out by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Designed for all users, regardless of prior experience.</li>
            <li><strong>Interactivity:</strong> Offers real-time simulations and an intuitive 3D interface.</li>
            <li><strong>Gamification:</strong> Employs gamified learning pathways to enhance engagement.</li>
            <li><strong>Integration:</strong> Combines advanced tools into a seamless, user-friendly platform.</li>
            <li><strong>Community Focus:</strong> Encourages collaboration and sharing among users.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>What support resources are available?</summary>
        <p>- <strong>Tutorials and Documentation:</strong> Comprehensive guides to help you navigate and utilize all features.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Customer Support:</strong> Reach out via email or live chat for assistance.</p>
        <p>- <strong>FAQs:</strong> A searchable database of frequently asked questions.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Community Forums:</strong> Engage with other users and find answers.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>Who is behind SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD is developed by a dedicated team of neuroscientists, software engineers, and innovators passionate about making neurotechnology accessible. Our combined expertise drives the platform's continuous growth and advancement.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How can I stay updated on SCI-NAD's developments?</summary>
        <p>- <strong>Newsletter:</strong> Subscribe to our newsletter for the latest news and updates.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Social Media:</strong> Follow us on platforms like Twitter, LinkedIn, and Facebook.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Blog:</strong> Read in-depth articles, tutorials, and insights on our blog.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Events:</strong> Join webinars, workshops, and conferences hosted by SCI-NAD.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How does SCI-NAD support researchers?</summary>
        <p>SCI-NAD provides researchers with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Advanced Simulation Tools:</strong> Run complex neural simulations with high accuracy.</li>
            <li><strong>Data Integration:</strong> Import and analyze custom datasets.</li>
            <li><strong>Collaboration Features:</strong> Work with peers and share findings within the platform.</li>
            <li><strong>Resource Access:</strong> Connect to a vast repository of research papers and datasets through integrated knowledge graphs.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>Is SCI-NAD suitable for use in professional research and publications?</summary>
        <p>Yes, SCI-NAD is designed to meet the needs of professional researchers:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Scientific Rigor:</strong> Utilizes validated tools and methodologies.</li>
            <li><strong>Data Export:</strong> Ability to export results and visualizations for use in publications.</li>
            <li><strong>Citation Support:</strong> Easy referencing of datasets and tools used within SCI-NAD.</li>
            <li><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Facilitate multi-institutional research projects through shared simulations and models.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How do gamified learning pathways work in SCI-NAD?</summary>
        <p>Gamified learning pathways guide users through progressively challenging modules:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Level Progression:</strong> Start with foundational concepts and advance to complex simulations.</li>
            <li><strong>Interactive Challenges:</strong> Engage in tasks that reinforce learning objectives.</li>
            <li><strong>Rewards and Badges:</strong> Earn recognition for achievements and milestones.</li>
            <li><strong>Adaptive Learning:</strong> Personalized recommendations based on your progress and interests.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>What kind of content can users share on the SCI-NAD marketplace?</summary>
        <p>Users can share:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Brain-Electrode Montages:</strong> Custom electrode placements and configurations.</li>
            <li><strong>Neural Simulations:</strong> Unique simulations of neural activity.</li>
            <li><strong>Educational Materials:</strong> Tutorials, lesson plans, and guides.</li>
            <li><strong>Custom Tools and Extensions:</strong> Plugins or scripts that enhance platform functionality.</li>
        </ul>
    </details>
    <details>
        <summary>How does SCI-NAD handle updates and new feature releases?</summary>
        <p>- <strong>Regular Updates:</strong> We continuously improve the platform with new features and enhancements.</p>
        <p>- <strong>User Feedback:</strong> Many updates are driven by community suggestions and needs.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Transparent Roadmap:</strong> Users can view our development roadmap and see what's coming next.</p>
        <p>- <strong>Seamless Integration:</strong> Updates are rolled out with minimal disruption to user experience.</p>
    </details>
</section>
